Title: Object: The principal street in Bethlehem
Series: Views in Egypt, Palestine and other parts of the Ottoman Empire
Description: Plate 19 in volume II: a crowd of men with turbans, women with veils, children with hats, many holding walking sticks, passing or resting by a street which leads to an arched gate; some standing in front of three shop windows on the right, talking with the shopkeepers; a landscape in the left background; after Mayer; published state. 1803 Hand-coloured aquatint with etching
Bibliographic references: Abbey Travel / Travel in Aquatint and lithography 1770-1860 from the library of J.R.Abbey (369.II.19)
